## 🐛 Bug Report

When using ExcelJS to load and save an Excel file without modifications, files containing a cell with text formatted as a custom date format (e.g mmm-yy) and another cell referencing it (e.g., =<CELL>) become corrupted. Upon opening the saved file in Microsoft Excel, a warning appears:
"We found a problem with some content in yyyy. Do you want us to recover as much as we can?"

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

Create an Excel file (test.xlsx) with the following setup:

Cell A1: Enter any text (e.g "test") and apply a custom cell format mmm-yy via Right click > Format Cells > Custom > mmm-yy.
Cell A2: Enter the formula =A1.

load and save the file using exceljs:


```javascript
        function load_and_save(file) {
            try {
                const workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
                const arrayBuffer = await file.arrayBuffer();
                await workbook.xlsx.load(await arrayBuffer);
                const buffer = await workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer();

                return buffer;
            } catch (error) {
                console.error('error:', error);
                throw error;
            }
        }
```

Windows 10 
